14 Nov 2010 05:35






That Operation wasn't so much a test as an attempt to secure the city by force because of its potential value. The nuke was on standby as a panic button. Detonation of the nuke would likely have killed the performers keeping the city up, meaning to check, the score would need to be performed again. So doing would manifest another instance of the entity, making the actual efficacy of the nuke a metaphysical consideration. At least, that's how I thought of it. As far as the Foundation would be concerned, they'd simply see the entity as unaffected the next time the score was played.

You do raise a good point, though. I'll see about cutting the nuke and taking another approach. Thanks for the feedback.







